This food is amazing

I came here 7 years ago and I just found myself thinking about how amazing the food was. I just came here to check and make sure it’s still open. Can’t wait to visit when I hopefully go back to San Fran next year. Yummmmmmm

Last week was our first time we came to that place. But It is absolutely not the last time. We had great time with the efficient service, with the excellent  cuisine and fine drinks and with the modest price. We will no doubt visit there soon.

This is doubtless one of the most pleasant place in the region. Anytime I come there I am extremely happy. They preserve their very high  level service and the highest level of food  they provide. You definitely will enjoy this this place. Very  recommended.

One of the cutest restaurants ever! It was a serendipitous occasion since I was just looking for somewhere to eat that was close to the Greek Theater. The restaurant resembles someone's living room and there was even some lovely live piano music.

Went here yesterday to grab a quick lunch. I had their Tapsilog and I also got a 'budget' size monggo. The monggo had amapalaya/bittermelon in it which was surprisingly really good for someone who doesn't eat ampalaya. The Tapsilog with the sweet tangy vinegar was delicious!
I didn't really like the food. Perhaps I just don't like Filipino food though.  The people were very nice and helpful in understanding the menu, though.

I admire this restaurant! They provide marvelous meals, their menu is large, The chief cook in that place is a professional, I like very much trying all their dishes. The dishes are consistently of high qualtity, the attitude towards the …
Highly recommend for a quick bite to eat. They were helpful in making sense of an unfamiliar menu. I'll definitely stop by again if I'm in the area.

I like this place! They serve fantastic dishes, their menu is varied, The chef in that place is a real authority in the kitchen, I enjoy a lot eating all their dishes. The dishes are consistently tasty, the service towards the clients  is nice. I visit often this restaurant and I not even once was unsatisfied.  I highly recommend it.
I just liked their dishes. I always get fantastic service there. The place is well kept and the staff members are always nice. Keep up the good work.

Felt like I was eating food from my mom and late grandmother. I was staying near the area and wanted an early breakfast. This place was open at 7am and I'm glad Google lead me to it. Tosilog and Embotido hit the spot and kept me full for …
Loved it!!!! Food is fresh & tasty!!!

The food is always so good, I love the dinuguan so tasty.  Longsilog so fast and easy in the morning and the picadillo is good any time of day.

Lovely filipino cuisine food. Benignit..dinaguan..sisig..pancit..halo halo. Smells wonderful inside. The workers were nice. Our family dined in, but everytime that front door swung open... A brief rush of piss odor hit us while eating..

I adore this place. Great prices for SF, delicious variety of authentic Filipino food, and friendly staff & service who are patient with the utter novitiates to Filipino food :O (cash-only, but there's an ATM on premises!)

My favorite spot in the City. Small, almost unnoticeable, place on Ellis and Mason. Great Filipino food but also amazing service from Manny at the register and his wife behind the stove. My week isn't complete without at least a couple of visits.

Very well organised and welcoming spot. They serve large portions and for economical rates. I liked the meals a lot and the staff members were very attentive and chatty. Highly recommended.

Excellent Pinoy food. Tocino, Filipino menudo (NOT to be confused with the Mexican version). A word of caution: if you want tapa, what they make here is actually bistek at other places. They adjust some of their items to "American" tastes. They have good silogs ( choice of various meats with rice and fried egg).
This place never fails to impress. They serve great food for affordable pricing, there are no long waits even when the spot is full.
